      "content": "The fact that you are even contemplating this shows how deep the pain is, but it is a dangerous illusion to believe that leaving would bring any peace or resolve the debt. Your parents would rather face your grief and shame than lose you, and they will likely forgive your shortcomings because your life was their greatest asset in this situation. Please know that your current thoughts are a symptom of your trauma, not the only solution; connecting with a mental health crisis line right now is the single most important step to ensure you have support when the \"lies\" of recovery fail. You exist before the money, and your presence—however difficult it feels to acknowledge—is the only thing that can truly heal this mess.",
